    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b1ecb9b2_70d20220",
        "filename": "milo/backend/query_blamelist.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 1178685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-16T11:29:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes. I think that\u0027s logically correct.\nAnd it will be capped to the page size. So performance-wise it should be fine too.",
      "parentUuid": "59be6b8b_3589f6fb",
      "revId": "8c2149922aab81bb573bcf44b363d878ace373e1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "339a77bd_5a9943c0",
        "filename": "milo/backend/query_blamelist.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 1369089
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-16T22:14:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suppose this is an edge case, and we should show \"There is no blamelist because this is the first build\", instead of showing everything?\n\nI think maybe we can improve the performance of this for loop by:\n1. Find out the last ancestor build of the current build that has status !\u003d Infra Failure, Expired or Canceled\n2. Just return the array of commits up that ancestor build?",
      "parentUuid": "b1ecb9b2_70d20220",
      "revId": "8c2149922aab81bb573bcf44b363d878ace373e1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c798df55_f3932ed4",
        "filename": "milo/backend/query_blamelist.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 1178685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-17T01:56:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e 1. Find out the last ancestor build of the current build that has status !\u003d Infra Failure, Expired or Canceled\n\nThat\u0027s basically what the loop is doing now.\n\n\u003e 2. Just return the array of commits up that ancestor build?\nThe problem with that is the builds are not ordered. They do have a build number, but there\u0027s no guarantee that the build with a smaller build number is the predecessor of a build with a greater build number. For instance, if we retry an old build, the retry build will have a large build ID and an old associated commit.\nTherefore we have to iterate though the commits. If we iterate though the commit, we may as well just return only the commits that we just checked instead of finding the last ancestor build.",
      "parentUuid": "339a77bd_5a9943c0",
      "revId": "8c2149922aab81bb573bcf44b363d878ace373e1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "93ba1c22_874c13c0",
        "filename": "milo/backend/query_blamelist.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 1369089
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-17T02:18:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I got it. I just want to see if going through every commit, and making a datastore query for each commit the only option we have here (since it seems expensive to me). Do we have any other data (like commit position) that can help us make the decision?",
      "parentUuid": "c798df55_f3932ed4",
      "revId": "8c2149922aab81bb573bcf44b363d878ace373e1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6001b9b5_eda3bbe8",
        "filename": "milo/backend/query_blamelist.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 1178685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-18T00:59:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I looked into this. Not every build has a commit position.\nAnd I can\u0027t think of a way to reduce the number of queries.\nWe can, however, parallelising the queries to improvement the performance.\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "93ba1c22_874c13c0",
      "revId": "8c2149922aab81bb573bcf44b363d878ace373e1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2974ac36_dcc56a69",
        "filename": "milo/backend/query_blamelist.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 1369089
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-18T01:38:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think parallelising this may be a good idea, if the performance is slow (may be we can check with 1000 and see if the performance is ok?).\n\nDo we already have index for the fields we want to query?",
      "parentUuid": "6001b9b5_eda3bbe8",
      "revId": "8c2149922aab81bb573bcf44b363d878ace373e1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "87cd87f6_9a494088",
        "filename": "milo/backend/query_blamelist.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-18T02:44:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "parallelizing this sgtm; These are all independent queries so there\u0027s no benefit to doing them sequentially. I recommend WorkPool (https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/common/sync/parallel/workPool.go;l\u003d29?q\u003dWorkPool\u0026ss\u003dchromium) with a conservative number of workers (say, 8).\n\nI think practically speaking, most of these queries will come up empty, so you\u0027re just going to be paying the RPC overhead. You probably want to play with this for a very densely-populated builder and also a very empty builder to figure out what a good value is.",
      "parentUuid": "2974ac36_dcc56a69",
      "revId": "8c2149922aab81bb573bcf44b363d878ace373e1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6c364e87_ca684d8f",
        "filename": "milo/backend/query_blamelist.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 1178685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-18T07:35:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "implemented.\nDid some preliminary testing. With a blamelist that has ~40 commits.\nwhen the number of worker is 8, it cuts the execution time to about half.\nSetting the worker count to 16 doesn\u0027t seem to improve the performance.\nSetting the worker count to 4 only marginally increate the query time, maybe it will be more significant if we have a longer blamelist.\nI think 8 works is good enough. We can always tune the number later.",
      "parentUuid": "87cd87f6_9a494088",
      "revId": "8c2149922aab81bb573bcf44b363d878ace373e1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
